               <p>HENRY WRIGHT. I am a <rs id="t18300527-80-viclabel428" type="occupation">plasterer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300527-80-victim713 t18300527-80-viclabel428"></join>. I was at work in <placeName id="t18300527-80-crimeloc429">Cumberland-crescent, Bryanstone-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300527-80-crimeloc429" type="placeName" value="Cumberland-crescent, Bryanstone-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300527-80-crimeloc429" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300527-80-off426 t18300527-80-crimeloc429"></join>, and put my coat in the drawing-room; a person lived there: I did not see the prisoner till there was a cry of Stop thief! my coat was taken about two or three o'clock on the 21st of April.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300527-80-person714">
                  PHILIP 
                  RILEY
               <interp inst="t18300527-80-person714" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-80-person714" type="given" value="PHILIP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-80-person714" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was on duty in Hyde-park, and saw the prisoner running; I pursued, and took him - he had thrown down this coat before I saw him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300527-80-person715">
                  JOHN 
                  ANSTIS
               <interp inst="t18300527-80-person715" type="surname" value="ANSTIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-80-person715" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-80-person715" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner on the staircase of the house; he was a perfect stranger - I was at work there; I went into the front drawing-room, and heard some one run down stairs - I pursued, and saw the prisoner running with the coat, which he dropped about half way down Seymour-street; I took it up, and still pursued - he took off his own great coat while he ran, and dropped that; I took that up, and still pursued till he was taken.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to the door, and met a man with this coat; I bought it of him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300527-80-verdict430" type="verdictDescription">
